[after 1 second]
{nome} is a young student who grew up far from Milan, the city that once belonged to his family. The son of a former dictator who fell under the weight of the revolution, he was raised with the shadow of the past always behind him.<br>
[after 3 second]
His father taught him to believe in peace and democracy, while the world reminded him that his name is synonymous with tyranny.<br>
<br>
[after 6 second]
He has never truly known power, only its consequences. <br>
[after 7 second]
He has never commanded, only listened to stories about those who did. <br>
[after 8 second]
For years he has lived in anonymity, learning to be a stranger in his own history, to hide the blood that flows in his veins. <br>
[after 9 seconds]
But beneath the appearance of a normal boy, behind the eyes of a silent observer, something bigger is hidden: a broken legacy, a fire that has never completely died out.<br>
<br>
[after 14 seconds]
{name} is not a man of ideals, nor a party soldier.<br>
[after 15 seconds]
He is a product of division, raised between two worlds without belonging to either. <br>
[after 16 seconds]
But when he returns to Milan and sees what communism has done to the city, he understands an undeniable truth: without order, freedom is just an illusion.<br>
[after 20 seconds]
Perhaps his father's past is a condemnation. Or perhaps, it is a guide.<br>
<br>
{link to: 'inizio.1_en', label: 'Begin your Adventure'}
